Russian History, 2016 - 2019, Postgraduate student

International and European law, 2009 - 2014, Graduate





Work

Centrum für Soziale Investitionen und Innovationen (Forschungsstelle des Max-Weber-Instituts für Soziologie)
Position: Research assistant (Wissenschaftliche Hilfskräft). April 2022 – June 2024.
Duties: literature search and review, assistance in writing articles and applying for grants, site management, web scraping

Herder-Institut für historische Ostmitteleuropaforschung – Institut der Leibniz-Gemeinschaft, Digitale Forschungs- und Informationsinfrastrukturen
Position: Research assistant (Wissenschaftliche Hilfskräft). September 2023 – June 2024.
Duties: literature search and review, working with various OCR (optical character recognition) tools and testing them, writing Python scripts




Research interests
Eastern European history, Russian history, legal history, rural societies, customary law, local self-government, social history, sociology, digital humanities, digital methods in history, OCR, computer vision, data visualization



Skills
Python (Tesseract, Pandas, NumPy, Seaborn), R (ggplot2), Quarto, GIT, TEI, XML, CSS, Optical Character Recognition (Transkribus, eScriptorium, Google Vision API, OpenCV, spaCy, Nopaque, recognAIze). Software (MS Office, Visual Studio Code, RStudio, Jupyter Notebook, Docker)


Grants and scholarships

Graduate School Scholarship Programme 2018, provided by DAAD for funding a Ph.D. research project at the Heidelberg Graduate School for the Humanities and Social Sciences, Heidelberg University (2019 – 2023);
Research grant for doctoral students, provided by Deutsches Historisches Institut Moskau (February 2019 - March 2019);
Travel grant provided by 4EU+ Alliance and Erasmus+ programme (July 2022).



